import pandas as pd

arrest_tab = pd.read_csv("http://www.hcbravo.org/IntroDataSci/misc/BPD_Arrests.csv")

dat = arrest_tab[arrest_tab['Location 1'].notna()].copy()
dat['lat'] = dat['Location 1'].str.extract("\(([0-9\.\-]*).*\)", expand=False)
dat['lng'] = dat['Location 1'].str.extract("\(.*,(.*)\)", expand=False)
dat = dat.sample(n=2000)
dat

In [3]:
male_dat = dat[dat['sex'] == 'M']
female_dat = dat[dat['sex'] == 'F']
male_lat = list(male_dat['lat'].astype(float))
male_lng = list(male_dat['lng'].astype(float))
male_loc = list(zip(male_lat, male_lng))
female_lat = list(female_dat['lat'].astype(float))
female_lng = list(female_dat['lng'].astype(float))
female_loc = list(zip(female_lat, female_lng))
In [4]:
from ipyleaflet import Map, Circle

balto_map = Map(
    center=(39.29, -76.61),
    zoom=11
)


for i in range(len(male_loc)):
    loc = male_loc[i]
    color = 'blue'
    circle = Circle()
    circle.location = loc
    circle.radius = 1
    circle.color = color
    circle.fill_color = color

    balto_map.add_layer(circle)
    
for i in range(len(female_loc)):
    loc = female_loc[i]
    color = 'red'
    circle = Circle()
    circle.location = loc
    circle.radius = 1
    circle.color = color
    circle.fill_color = color

    balto_map.add_layer(circle)
In [10]:
balto_map

The map shows the location of crimes happened in Baltimore area with color representing the gender of the criminal. Specifically, red represents femail criminal and blue represents male criminal.
